1. Move .env.template to .env.
2. Fill out .env variables.
3. Build docker image with 'docker build --build-arg UID=$(id -u) --build-arg GID=$(id -g) -t kettlewright .'
4. Run 'docker run -it --user $(id -u):$(id -g) --env-file .env -v $(pwd)/migrations:/app/migrations -v $(pwd)/instance:/app/instance kettlewright /bin/sh'
5. Run 'flask db upgrade' and then 'exit'
6. Launch with 'docker run --user $(id -u):$(id -g) -v $(pwd):/app --env-file .env -p 5000:5000 kettlewright'
7. Access the application at http://127.0.0.1:5000
